snippet: Big names and big productions with corporate tie-ins were one thread at the South by Southwest festival, but lesser known acts still make up its core.
abstract: South by Southwest Music festival, long associated with little-known bands trying to break into industry, has also become host to big names and productions with corporate tie-ins; however, smaller acts still dominate festival.
lead_paragraph: Big names and big productions with corporate tie-ins were one thread at the South by Southwest festival, but lesser known acts still make up its core.
